# FPGA-Based ECG Arrhythmia Detection Using AMD Zynq-7000

## 1. Project Description

This repository contains the complete implementation of a hardware-accelerated ECG arrhythmia detection system deployed on the AMD Zynq-7000 SoC.
The system performs fixed-point neural network inference using a custom MLP accelerator synthesized via Vitis HLS and integrated into a Zynq hardware design. 
The design follows a full hardware-software co-design methodology.

Inference Pipeline:
ECG Beat (SD Card) → ARM Processing System → AXI → MLP Accelerator (PL) → Classification Result → UART Output

## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Processing System (PS)

- ARM Cortex-A9
- DDR Memory Controller
- SD Card Interface
- UART Peripheral
- AXI Interconnect

### 2.2 Programmable Logic (PL)

- Custom MLP Accelerator IP
- AXI Lite Control Interface
- AXI Memory-Mapped Data Interface
- DSP48-Based Multiply-Accumulate Units
- Fixed-Point Arithmetic (ap_fixed)

### 2.3 Data Flow

1. ECG beat data stored on SD card  
2. Data loaded into DDR memory  
3. Feature vector transmitted to accelerator via AXI  
4. Fixed-point matrix multiplication and activation computation  
5. Binary classification generated  
6. Result returned to ARM and transmitted over UART  


## 3. Machine Learning Implementation

### 3.1 Model Architecture

- Fully Connected Multi-Layer Perceptron
- Input Layer: ECG Beat Samples
- Hidden Layer: Dense Layer
- Output Layer: Binary Classification

### 3.2 Training

